sentences.english: Protesters also seized the country's state-owned television station.
sentences.chinese: 抗議羣衆還佔據了吉爾吉斯斯坦國營電視臺。

sentences.english: The charming and bashful claim of Kyrgyzstan is that it is the least known country in the world.
sentences.chinese: 吉爾吉斯斯坦的迷人之處在於人們對她瞭解很少。

sentences.english: A big earthquake occurred in the Republic of Kyrgystan in the Central Asian region.
sentences.chinese: 中亞地區的吉爾吉斯斯坦發生大地震。

sentences.english: Kyrgyzstan is a landlocked, mountainous country in Central Asia.
sentences.chinese: 吉爾吉斯斯坦是位於中亞的內陸國，境內多山。

sentences.english: Quick-footed diplomacy helped contain the troubles in Kyrgyzstan.
sentences.chinese: 捷足外交幫助控制了吉爾吉斯斯坦出現的騷亂。

sentences.english: The government of Kyrgyzstan asked parliament to approve the closure of an important American air base, Manas, near the capital, Bishkek.
sentences.chinese: 吉爾吉斯斯坦政府要求議會批准關閉美軍空軍基地。

sentences.english: Symbol of Power In Kyrgyzstan, five dams control the flow of water on the Naryn River.
sentences.chinese: 在吉爾吉斯斯坦，五個水壩控制水流的納倫河。

sentences.english: Behind all this lies the reality that the lingua franca in Kyrgyzstan is Russian.
sentences.chinese: 這一切的背後，吉爾吉斯斯坦通用語言卻是俄語。

sentences.english: Nearby, Kyrgyz soldiers had set up checkpoints in a post-facto show of strength.
sentences.chinese: 在附近，吉爾吉斯斯坦士兵設立了關卡。

sentences.english: That is also how many Kyrgyz feel about Mr Bakiev.
sentences.chinese: 大多數吉爾吉斯斯坦人民也覺得巴基耶夫令人失望。

sentences.english: Objective To study pharmacognosy of wild Glycyrrhiza aspera Pall.
sentences.chinese: 目的對吉爾吉斯斯坦野生粗毛甘草進行生藥學研究。
